creator: Mark Lemon
description: LibriVox volunteers bring you 17 recordings of How to Make a Man of Consequence by Mark Lemon. This was the Weekly Poetry project for June 29, 2014. Read in English by Andrew K Waugh; Algy Pug; Arup Sen; Anders Stigö; Bruce Kachuk; Claudia Salto; David Lawrence; Jason Mills; J Korth; Jannie Meisberger; Julia Niedermaier; Kimberly Hirsh; Lee Ann Howlett; Leonard Wilson; Rosslyn Carlyle; Ruth Golding and SkyAlbatross. Mark Lemon had a natural talent for journalism and the stage, and, at twenty-six, retired from less congenial business to devote himself to the writing of plays. More than sixty of his melodramas, operettas and comedies were produced in London, whilst at the same time he was contributing to a wide variety of magazines and newspapers, and was founding editor of both Punch and The Field. (Summary form Wikipedia) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. Download M4B (7MB)
